<h3>Is the quality of work done by offshore creative staff good enough?</h3>
<p>We find fantastic work quality in creative job roles like web designers, drafts people, architects, illustrators and finished artists. However, we find the labour talent pool in the Philippines for graphic designers is of a lower standard. This doesn’t mean that we can’t find good quality graphic designers, we can, it is just that they are more difficult to come by and is sometimes not up to western graphic design standards.</p>

<h3>Is the quality of work done by offshore Telemarketing staff good enough?</h3>
<p>Telemarketing is not a preferred career choice for many local Australians. Often when you place job ads on seek, you get few enquires. Students and travellers are often the only applicants willing to do this line of work.</p>

<p>The Philippines is emerging to be the global choice with Telemarketing because many people in the Philippines treat outbound and inbound telemarketing roles as a career move and are committed in doing whatever it takes to get the job done right. We find many telemarketers in the market place who have years of experience with American & Australian people.</p>

<p>You will find good results using telemarketers from the Philippines. Many people in the market place are eager to respond to email or phone enquiries, provide technical and/or customer support, up-sell, cross-sell other products, transfer phone calls to appropriate departments after qualifying the call, take care of account and billing enquiries, market a product or a service, sell a product or a service over the phone, appointment-setting and market research.</p>

<h3>Can I really trust offshore staff?</h3>
<p>Yes, you can. At Remote Staff, we have created systems to help build trust. This is achieved with our invoice system. Clients pay one month in advance and the offshore staff get paid one month in the rear only after they have satisfied the job requirements. Trust is also formed with communications; we require offshore staff to be in contact with us at all times. If they do not show up to work for some reason, we must be informed about it. Our HR manager will always be in touch with your offshore staff.</p>

<p>We also have a 3-minute Skype chat rule. Any time you use instant Skype chat messenger services, offshore staff have to respond to your online communications within 3 minutes. We found as long as communication is instant, trust is built. We also give offshore staff local Australian phone numbers for those clients that want to be able to pick up the phone and call them.</p>

<p>But it’s the Remote Staff system that really helps you build trust with the use of the screen snapshots every 5 minutes. This will help you monitor their daily work flow activities as well as help manage them. In addition to that, you will be able to see their online time sheets including when they start, finish and take lunch.</p>

<p>Also, we have a full time HR manager you can contact any time. Her job is to confirm your staff are online and on-time working.</p>

<h3>Will offshore staff working from home do less work and take longer to get a job done compared with staff working in an office?</h3>
<p>In 90% of cases, we find offshore staff about to keep productivity levels high when working from home. Offshore staff working from home is a preferred choice for many applicants because they get to spend more time at home and can avoid the heavy pollution and massive traffic jams. Remote Staff working from home start their work day fresh. We find by the end of the day staffs are not as tired which increases their productivity levels for you compared to staff working from one of the offices.</p>

<p>In some cases, you will find work from home production can drop by 40% simply because some offshore staff are just not able to adjust with the idea of working from home. They get distracted by family and friends and other things. It’s not a problem if this happens because it would be evident to you as the client and our HR manager in the first week or two. In these cases, we will replace your staff member right away. Our experiences suggest this happens only 10% of the time.</p>

<p>If you don’t want staff working from home, we have 250 office seats available to lease out at $400 per month. Often, having staff working from an office is a good idea when you have a team of 20+ staff. One key benefit in using offshore staff to work from an office is with the reliable power and internet connection. We do have all offshore staff set up working from home with broadband ADSL internet connection. When staff work at home, sometimes you will find blackouts or simple internet drop outs occur once every few weeks. Having staff in an office will prevent this from happening.</p>

<h3>Will they be effective, efficient and functional for my business?</h3>
<p>Yes, they can be just like a local staff member if you are prepared to train and work with your remote staff in the initial stages of employment and the results will speak for themselves in no time. Please note, using offshore staff to work remotely for you will never be a perfect, risk free, secure unconditional satisfaction guaranteed type of experience. It just isn’t. However, once you have the remote staff working the way you want them to you will be pleasantly surprised at just how much extra leverage you and your team can get with the use of offshore staff working for your business remotely.</p>

<h3>Will using offshore staff be a negative reflection of my business; is this something that is very Un-Australian?</h3>
<p>At first glance, it’s easy to see outsourcing as taking local jobs away from Australians but outsourcing and using offshore staff isn’t about that. Remote Staff is about adding new productivity and capabilities for businesses that may not have been able to achieve such capacities by employing just locally. It’s about strengthening and making local businesses competitive in the global market place. Remote Staff often helps businesses get stronger and in turn establishes new employment opportunities locally.</p>

<p>At Think Innovations, we speak with lots of Australian businesses about using Remote Staff and find many Australian companies have been outsourcing and using offshore staff in some way. It’s not just large corporations using offshore staff as a competitive advantage, solo entrepreneurs and consultants are now using this new global trend.</p>

<p>Australians are right now in contact with offshore staff in their everyday lives, and it’s becoming more and more culturally acceptable to get a call from someone offshore about their Optus phone bills, internet connections with Dodo or Citibank credit cards. All of these large companies use offshore staff located in the Philippines to increase their competitive advantages.</p>





